issues.description:
Function _0x0000006e2b22_lets_not_compete__821() retrieves the transaction origin (tx.origin) using the ORIGIN opcode. Use msg.sender instead.
See also: https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/security-considerations.html#tx-origin
issues.title: Use of tx.origin

issues.description:
The function `_0x0000006e2b22_lets_not_compete__821()` executes the SUICIDE instruction. The remaining Ether is sent to: origin

It seems that this function can be called without restrictions.
issues.title: Unchecked SUICIDE
